  "issue_number": 145,
  "issue_title": "[bug] audit: read_recent_executed_actions returns empty with no log on IO failure",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\n`AuditLogger::read_recent_executed_actions` returns an empty `Vec` when the audit file cannot be opened, with no log line. Undo / \u201cwhat did you do?\u201d flows then behave as if no actions ever ran, which is misleading and distinct from \u201caudit disabled.\u201d\n\n#131 covers **append** silent failures; this issue is **read** path observability.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create an unreadable audit file:\n\n   ```bash\n   touch /tmp/genie-audit.jsonl\n   chmod 000 /tmp/genie-audit.jsonl\n   ```\n\n2. Configure genie-core to use that path (or chmod the live audit file).\n\n3. Trigger a path that calls `read_recent_executed_actions` (undo / \u201cwhat did you do?\u201d / dispatch reload).\n\n4. Observe: returns `[]`; no `tracing::warn!` or `tracing::error!`.\n\nSmoking gun \u2014 `crates/genie-core/src/tools/actuation.rs` ~L326\u2013L331:\n\n```rust\nlet Ok(file) = File::open(path) else {\n    return Vec::new();\n};\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- On open failure: `tracing::warn!` or `tracing::error!` with path and `io::Error` kind (`journalctl -u genie-core`).\n- Readable audit file with `Executed` events \u2192 unchanged behavior.\n- Optional in PR: `Result<Vec<RecordedAction>>` to distinguish empty vs error (discuss breaking change).\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n`File::open` failure is swallowed; returns empty `Vec` with no log. Operators cannot tell \u201cno recent actuations\u201d from \u201caudit unreadable (permissions, disk, path).\u201d\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n`v1.0.0-alpha.9 / main @ crates/genie-core/src/tools/actuation.rs`\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**Severity:** Reliability / observability \u2014 not a security bypass. Fails \u201copen\u201d from the user\u2019s perspective (undo unavailable) but hides the real failure mode from operators and support.\n\n**Split from #131 on purpose:**\n| Path | Issue | Symptom |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| Append | #131 | Events never written; audit file empty/stale |\n| Read (this) | \u2014 | File exists but unreadable; callers see `[]` as if history were empty |\n\n**Suggested PR (minimal):**\n1. On `File::open` failure: `tracing::warn!(path = %path.display(), error = %e, \"audit read failed\")`.\n2. Optionally log parse failures at `debug!` with rate limit (separate from open).\n3. Unit test: `tempfile` + `chmod 000` (Unix) \u2192 assert log or `Result::Err` if you change the API.\n4. Defer `Result<Vec<RecordedAction>>` to a follow-up unless maintainers want a breaking change in one PR.\n\n**Call sites to sanity-check after logging:** `ToolDispatcher` reload of recent actions (~`dispatch.rs`), undo / \u201cwhat did you do?\u201d quick routes.\n\n**Real Behavior Proof:** `cargo test -p genie-core` + optional manual chmod on audit path under `GENIEPOD_CONFIG`.\n\n**Related:** [#131](https://github.com/GeniePod/genie-claw/issues/131), [#24](https://github.com/GeniePod/genie-claw/issues/24) (evidence trails \u2014 integrity needs observable read *and* write).",
